Generate a Client Trace ID to Troubleshoot Non-Pub/Sub API Errors

To help you troubleshoot errors that don't originate from the Pub/Sub API service and don't include an RPC ID, use the custom x-client-trace-id metadata header. Add x-client-trace-id metadata to every RPC request the client makes to Pub/Sub API as part of the authorization headers. Typical non-Pub/Sub API errors include network errors or errors returned from the data center infrastructure.

Where: This change applies to Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer editions. Pub/Sub API isnâ€™t available in Government Cloud.
